text: Lakselvbukt is a small village located in the Tromsø Municipality of Troms county in Norway. It is situated on the inner part of the Ullsfjorden and is around northeast of the village of Laksvatn in the neighboring Balsfjord Municipality. The village is also located near the western edge of the Lyngen Alps, which is around away from the city of Tromsø. The Lakselvbukt Church is located on the outskirts of the village. == References == Category:Villages in Norway Category:Settlements in Troms
title: Lakselvbukt
